defaultI believe that I have provided compelling evidence to support a position where it is vital that there is  a continuing
default duty on the Senior President of Tribunals to report on the standards of decision making by the DWP following the abolition of the Administrative Justice and Tribunals Council and the merger of the Tribunals Service with HM Courts Service.
defaultMy understanding is that 
defaultProfessor Harrington’s recommendation for the First Tier to report in detail on Appeal cases was accepted by both the Ministry of Justice and by the DWP.  So surely this position still stands and the role previously put on the Council therefore still stands?
